<body>
  <header>
    <h1>Technical SEO Guide 2025 – Improve Speed, Structure & Core Web Vitals</h1>
    <p><em>Published: August 29, 2025 | Author: Ellie Brewster</em></p>
  </header>

  <article>
    <h2>1. Core Web Vitals</h2>
    <p>
      Google’s Core Web Vitals remain a top ranking factor in 2025. Focus on <strong>LCP, CLS, and INP</strong>
      to ensure fast loading, visual stability, and quick interactivity. Tools like PageSpeed Insights and Lighthouse
      are essential for monitoring.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Mobile-First Indexing</h2>
    <p>
      With mobile-first indexing fully rolled out, your site must deliver the same structured data,
      meta tags, and high-quality content on both desktop and mobile versions.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Site Architecture & Crawl Budget</h2>
    <p>
      A clean URL structure and logical hierarchy help Google crawl and index efficiently.
      Avoid deep nesting and keep important pages within three clicks from the homepage.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Schema Markup</h2>
    <p>
      Implement <strong>structured data</strong> for articles, products, and services.
      Schema increases your chance of rich snippets and higher CTR in SERPs.
    </p>

    <h2>5. Indexing & Robots.txt</h2>
    <p>
      Use robots.txt and noindex tags wisely. Ensure only valuable pages are indexed,
      and block duplicate or thin content.
    </p>

    <h2>Conclusion</h2>
    <p>
      Technical SEO in 2025 is about providing <strong>speed, accessibility, and structured clarity</strong>.
      Sites that nail these fundamentals will secure better rankings and user trust.
    </p>
  </article>

